26/09/2007
BELGRADE, Serbia -- NATO has told the government the exact locations of cluster bombs dropped during the 1999 air campaign against Yugoslavia, Belgrade media reported on Tuesday (September 25th). 
The foreign ministry confirmed that it had received a list of sites from NATO headquarters in Brussels. 
More than 1,000 cluster bombs were dropped on 219 locations. 
Mine-clearing experts will be sent to those areas to look for unexploded ordnance. 
Serbia hopes the international community will help fund the effort. 
(AP, UPI, Tanjug, B92, RTS, DPA, Earthtimes.org - 25/09/07)
